IRS990.Description: FAMILY MEDICINE: IN ITS WESTERN MAINE FAMILY PRACTICE AND OXFORD HILLS FAMILY PRACTICE PROGRAMS, DURING FISCAL YEAR 2010 WMMMS EMPLOYED FIVE FAMILY MEDICINE PHYSICIANS AND TWO NURSE PRACTITIONERS. OUR FAMILY MEDICINE PROGRAM PROVIDED CARE TO PATIENTS DURING 20,505 VISITS IN THE PHYSICIAN OFFICE AND AT LOCAL LONG-TERM CARE FACILITIES. FAMILY MEDICINE PHYSICIANS ALSO PROVIDED CARE DURING AN ADDITIONAL 1,850 VISITS TO HOSPITALIZED PATIENTS. SEE ATTACHED COMMUNITY BENEFIT STATEMENT.

Activity2.Description: OBSTETRICS AND GYNECOLOGY: IN ITS WESTERN MAINE OB/GYN PRACTICE, DURING FISCAL YEAR 2010 WMMMS EMPLOYED THREE OB/GYN PHYSICIANS. OUR OB/GYN PROGRAM PROVIDED CARE TO PATIENTS DURING 6,171 PHYSICIAN-OFFICE PATIENT VISITS. THESE PHYSICIANS ALSO DELIVERED 187 BABIES AND PERFORMED 816 SURGICAL PROCEDURES.

Activity3.Description: PEDIATRICS: IN ITS WESTERN MAINE PEDIATRICS PRACTICE, DURING FISCAL YEAR 2010 WMMMS EMPLOYED FOUR PEDIATRICIANS AND ONE NURSE PRACTITIONER. OUR PEDIATRICS PROGRAM PROVIDED CARE TO PATIENTS DURING 13,446 PHYSICIAN-OFFICE PATIENT VISITS. PEDIATRICIANS ALSO PROVIDED CARE DURING AN ADDITIONAL 271 VISITS TO HOSPITALIZED PATIENTS INCLUDING NEWBORNS.

ActivityOther.Description: OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES INCLUDE GENERAL SURGERY PHYSICIAN PRACTICE; SEASONAL MEDICAL CLINIC AT A LOCAL SKI RESORT; SCHOOL-BASED HEALTH CLINICS LOCATED IN A MIDDLE SCHOOL AND A HIGH SCHOOL; AND OFFICE-BASED CARDIOLOGY AND PSYCHIATRY CONSULTATION SERVICES.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: DECISIONS SUBJECT TO APPROVAL OF MEMBERS
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: ALL DECISIONS BY THE WESTERN MAINE MULTI-MEDICAL SPECIALISTS' GOVERNING BODY ARE APPROVED BY DEFAULT BY THE MEMBER ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING BODY. THIS IS BECAUSE THESE TWO ORGANIZATIONS SHARE A COMMON GOVERNING BODY.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS USED TO REVIEW FORM 990
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE 990 WAS REVIEWED IN DETAIL BY A COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES. THE PRESIDENT AND SENIOR VICE PRESIDENT - FISCAL LED THE DISCUSSION. SUBSEQUENT TO THAT REVIEW, A COPY OF THE ORGANIZATION'S 990 WAS DISTRIBUTED TO ALL TRUSTEES. THE 990 WAS REVIEWED IN SUMMARY AT A BOARD MEETING PRIOR TO FILING.

CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS ARE OBTAINED ANNUALLY. THE PRESIDENT'S OFFICE COLLECTS AND REVIEWS THEM. WHERE ANY REAL OR PERCEIVED CONFLICTS EXIST, OFFICERS AND TRUSTEES ARE EXPECTED TO RECUSE THEMSELVES (1) FROM MEETINGS DURING TIMES WHEN THE TOPICS OF POTENTIAL CONFLICT ARE DISCUSSED AND (2) FROM VOTING ON SUCH MATTERS. KEY EMPLOYEES MAY NOT USE THEIR POSITIONS TO PROFIT PERSONALLY OR TO ASSIST OTHERS IN PROFITING IN ANY WAY AT THE EXPENSE OF WESTERN MAINE MULTI-MEDICAL SPECIALISTS.

THE PARENT COMPANY OF WESTERN MAINE MULTI-MEDICAL SPECIALISTS IS WESTERN MAINE HEALTH CARE, CORP. (EIN 01-0411788) WHO THROUGH ITS PARENT COMPANY MAINEHEALTH, HAS A FORMAL WRITTEN COMPENSATION POLICY IN PLACE. IN CONSULTATION WITH TOWERS PERRIN, THE MAINEHEALTH BOARD COMPENSATION COMMITTEE ESTABLISHES APPROPRIATE COMPENSATION PARAMETERS FOR EACH ORGANIZATION'S CEO AND CERTAIN MEMBERS OF THEIR SENIOR MANAGEMENT TEAM. WORKING WITHIN THESE PARAMETERS, THE WESTERN MAINE HEALTH CARE BOARD DETERMINES THE LEVEL OF COMPENSATION FOR ITS CEO. THE FINDINGS OF THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE ARE MADE TRANSPARENT TO, AND VOTED ON BY, THE FULL GOVERNING BOARD. THE "TOTAL EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION" IS FILED PUBLICLY BY THE ORGANIZATION, AND INCLUDES "TOTAL CASH COMPENSATION" AND "TOTAL VALUE OF ALL BENEFITS AND PERQUISITES" ASSOCIATED WITH THE POSITION. THE BOARD TAKES NECESSARY ACTION TO PREVENT THE CEO FROM VOTING OR DIRECTLY PARTICIPATING IN THE FINAL COMMITTEE DETERMINATION OF HIS OWN COMPENSATION. THE ORGANIZATION'S EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION PROCEDURES RELY UPON APPROPRIATE DATA FOR COMPARABILITY (E.G. COMPENSATION LEVELS PAID BY BOTH TAXABLE AND TAX-EXEMPT SIMILARLY SITUATED ORGANIZATIONS AND INDEPENDENT SURVEYS BY NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED INDEPENDENT FIRMS). FINALLY, THE ORGANIZATION REFRAINS FROM ALLOWING EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION TO EVER BE BASED SOLEY ON WESTERN MAINE HEALTH CARE, CORP.'S REVENUES OR OTHER SIMILAR PROFIT-SHARING STRATEGIES.
DOCUMENTS THAT ARE REQUIRED TO BE OPEN FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION ARE MADE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
